Class SimpleReadableMedia

    public final class SimpleReadableMedia

      • readRest

        public byte[] readRest()
                throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: ReadableMedia
        Reads the rest of object data till end marker. This method may only be called from UserTypeInput i.e. after user type marker is extracted from input. This method is designed to support different versions of object binaries.
        Specified by:
        readRest in interface ReadableMedia
        Returns:
        the rest of object (this may be empty array)
        Throws:
        IOException - if reading error occurred (like end of stream, etc)
